Introduction

Busters, also known as Power Busters, is a Korean girl group consisting of five members and run by Marbling E&M and JTG Entertainment. The group currently consists of Jieun, Seira, Takara, Minji and Nami. The members are also part of the project group MyBling, a collaboration between Mydoll Entertainment and Marbling.

The group originally debuted in 2017, but disbanded on August 6, 2020, after all original members left the company. All activities between the debut and the dissolution in 2020 are now under the name Busters β (Busters Beta). Power Busters also has a storyline with each of the five members being superheroes. This was supposed to be made into a film or TV series since the original line-up was decided in 2017, but so far the only development has been a small comic book feature on EBS Toon in late 2020.

The band reappeared on 27 April 2022 with the mini album "Re:Born".
